com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin

Class Assembler.Callback

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.Assembler.Callback
  • Enclosing class:
    Assembler

    public abstract static class Assembler.Callback
extends Object
    Used for assembly algorithms to provide results back to Geneious. A callback is supplied to the assembly algorithm via Assembler.assemble(Options, AssemblerInput, jebl.util.ProgressListener, com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.Assembler.Callback)

      • addContigDocument

        public abstract void addContigDocument(SequenceAlignmentDocument contig,
                     NucleotideSequenceDocument contigConsensus,
                     boolean isThisTheOnlyContigGeneratedByDeNovoAssembly,
                     ProgressListener progressListener)
                                throws DocumentOperationException
        Adds a contig generated by this assembler.
        Parameters:
        contig - the generated contig. If the assembler returned Assembler.ContigOutputSupport.ConsensusOnly from Assembler.getContigOutputSupport() this may be null.
        contigConsensus - the consensus of the generated contig. If the assembler returned Assembler.ContigOutputSupport.ContigsOnly from Assembler.getContigOutputSupport() this may be null.
        progressListener - progress for Geneious to report to while it saves the data to the user's local database.
        isThisTheOnlyContigGeneratedByDeNovoAssembly - if this is a de novo (rather than reference sequence) assembly and only a single result is being generated, this should be true to assist Geneious in naming the results more appropriately. If in doubt set this to false.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if the document cannot be saved.

               ProgressListener progressListener)

      • addDocument

        public void addDocument(AnnotatedPluginDocument document,
               ProgressListener progressListener)
                 throws DocumentOperationException
        Adds a document generated by this assembler. This document will not be mentioned in the assembler report. This should not be a contig or unused read. In most situations, assemblers should use addContigDocument or addUnusedRead or addUnusedReads or addAssemblyReportText instead.
        Parameters:
        document - the document to add
        progressListener - progress for Geneious to report to while it saves the data to the user's local database.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if the document cannot be saved.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if this callback doesn't implement this method
        Since:
        API 4.3.0 (Geneious 5.3.0)

      • addUnusedReads

        public void addUnusedReads(SequenceListDocument unusedReads,
                  ProgressListener progressListener)
                    throws DocumentOperationException
        Adds a list of reads that were not assembled. An assembler should only call this if it returned true from Assembler.providesUnusedReads().

        This is a convenience method whose functionality is implemented as a series of calls to addUnusedRead(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.AssemblerInput.Read, jebl.util.ProgressListener) and is intended for use with assembly algorithms which call external command line programs which return unused reads in a file which is imported into Geneious as a SequenceListDocument.

        Parameters:
        unusedReads - the unused reads.
        progressListener - progress for Geneious to report to while it saves the data to the user's local database.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if the document cannot be saved.

      • setNumberOfMappedReads

        public void setNumberOfMappedReads(long numberOfMappedReads)
        Informs the callback of the total number of reads mapped. If a read is mapped to multiple locations, it should only be counted once towards this total.
        Parameters:
        numberOfMappedReads - the total number of reads mapped.
        Since:
        API 4.902 (Geneious 9.0.2)

      • addAssemblyReportText

        public void addAssemblyReportText(String textAsHtmlFragment)
        Adds some text to be included in the assembly report (if the user chooses to generate or display one).
        Parameters:
        textAsHtmlFragment - the text to display in the report which should be an html fragment. (i.e. < and > are treated as html tags)
